Hosting static website with github pages
source : https://pages.github.com/

step 1 : Login to your github account.
step 2 : create a public repository with your name.
         ex: yourname.github.io
step 3 : Clone newly created repo to your local.
step 4 : Create and commit your static website as index.html.
step 5 : Push your code to github.
step 6 : Go to setting section of your repository (top right, gear symbol).
step 7 : Scroll down to github page section.
step 8 : Modify source tab from none to master branch and save.
step 9 : Wait for it and scroll over to github pages section and copy the url generated by github for you.
step 10 : Open link in seperate window to see your website.